ky-Q-60557137" data-toc="1">Should you buy Sky Glass, Sky Stream, or Sky Q?</h2></div><div class="text-description"><p>Settling on the best Sky TV deal is a little tougher than it used to be since Sky now offers&nbsp;<em>three</em>&nbsp;difference boxes to watch its exclusive live channels, on-demand, and movies. Before you even start to think about the bundle of channels and optional extras that would be best suited to your tastes ...you'll need to decide on a set-top box.</p><p>Sky offers three hardware options: <strong>Sky Glass, Sky Stream, </strong>and<strong> Sky Q</strong>.</p><p>Below, we've compared the features and performance of these competing boxes to help you find the best fit for your home.</p></div><div class="text-description"><h2 id="Why-Sky-Stream-60557139" data-toc="0">Why Sky Stream?</h2></div><div class="text-description"><p>Sky Stream is the most recent addition to the lineup.</p><p>It's powered by Sky's custom-designed EntertainmentOS &ndash; just like Sky Glass, so you'll find the same menu design and&nbsp;software tricks across both devices. But while Sky Glass is an all-in-one QLED TV, Sky Stream squeezes everything into a palm-sized box that can be plugged into <em>any</em> television around your home.</p><p>As such, Sky Stream really feels like the next-generation successor to the likes of the Sky Q box. If you don't want the expense of buying a new QLED TV or are perfectly happy with your current set-up, Sky Stream is a superb choice.</p><p>As the name suggests, there's no need for a satellite dish on the outside of your home with everything streamed over a Wi-Fi connection. That means anyone who lives in an apartment building without a communal dish or a rented property will be able to watch Sky TV for the first time ...although you will need a halfway decent broadband connection.</p><p>Sky Stream is available as part of an 18-month contract &ndash; like Sky Q or traditional Sky+ HD boxes &ndash; or with a 31-day rolling contract. While the latter costs a little more, it means you'll be able to subscribe and cancel Sky TV multiple times throughout the year, just like Netflix or Sky-owned NOW (formerly NOW TV).</p><p>If you want to stream exclusive shows like <em>The Last Of Us</em>,&nbsp;<em>House of the Dragon, Gangs of London, The White Lotus,</em>&nbsp;and <em>The Rehearsal</em> as they air on Sky each week, Sky Stream will let you watch in crisp Ultra HD, HDR, and Dolby Atmos surround sound.</p><p>Bundled with Sky Stream, you'll find the same next-generation remote control that ships with Sky Glass.</p><p>That means you'll get backlit buttons to make late-night viewing easier, as well as voice commands to find new shows, movies with your favourite actor, and open streaming services built into the set-top box, like Netflix, Disney+, Apple TV+, Prime Video, and more.</p><p>Want to know whether Sky Stream can compete with Sky Glass or Sky Q? Our in-depth <a data-link-tracking="InArticle|Link" href="/sky-stream-review" rel="tag"><strong>Sky Stream review</strong></a> has&nbsp;<em>all</em> of the answers.</p><p>With an 18-month contract, Sky Stream costs exactly the same as Sky Q &ndash; <a data-link-tracking="InArticle|Link" href="https://www.awin1.com/cread.php?awinmid=11005&amp;awinaffid=213635&amp;campaign=&amp;clickref=Express---ExpressTech-&amp;clickref2=&amp;clickref3=&amp;clickref4=&amp;clickref5=&amp;clickref6=&amp;ued=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sky.com%2Fglass%2Fbuy%2Fstream%2Ftv-packs&amp;pl=la" rel="nofollow" onclick="ExpressApp.GoogleAnalytics.TrackEvent('Affiliate NetworkEvent', 'AWIN')"><strong>&pound;26 per month</strong></a> with an 18-month contract. Although it's worth noting that Sky Q arrives with 300 live channels whereas Sky Stream viewers only get 150 channels to watch. The latter are <em>all</em> in 1080p HD at no extra cost, something Sky Q owners still have to pay for!</p><p>Both of these options include a Netflix and discovery+ subscription for free (worth &pound;6.99 per month<em> each</em> when bought separately) access to exclusive shows from US streamer Peacock, 500 on-demand boxsets from HBO and Sky Originals. If you want the same bundle with a 31-day rolling contract via Sky Stream, you'll need to pay <a data-link-tracking="InArticle|Link" href="https://www.awin1.com/cread.php?awinmid=11005&amp;awinaffid=213635&amp;campaign=&amp;clickref=Express---ExpressTech-&amp;clickref2=&amp;clickref3=&amp;clickref4=&amp;clickref5=&amp;clickref6=&amp;ued=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sky.com%2Fglass%2Fbuy%2Fstream%2Ftv-packs&amp;pl=la" rel="nofollow" onclick="ExpressApp.GoogleAnalytics.TrackEvent('Affiliate NetworkEvent', 'AWIN')"><strong>&pound;29 per month</strong></a>.</p></div><div class="buying-guide" id="buying-guide-12" data-id="12" data-single="0" data-name="Sky Stream *UPDATED SEPT 29, 23*"><div class="widget blurb"><div class="data"><h3 class="title">Sky Stream</h3><h4 class="title">The Cutting-Edge Features Of Sky Glass, Available On Any TV</h4><div class="bg-stars" title="5 / 5"> <span class="star star-filled"></span> <span class="star star-filled"></span> <span class="star star-filled"></span> <span class="star star-filled"></span> <span class="star star-filled"></span></div><div class="columns"><div class="images"> <picture class="image"> <source type="image/avif" srcset="https://cdn.images.express.co.uk/img/dynamic/buyingguides/400x240/1688741381729.avif"> <source type="image/webp" srcset="https://cdn.images.express.co.uk/img/dynamic/buyingguides/400x240/1688741381729.webp"> <img src="https://cdn.images.express.co.uk/img/dynamic/buyingguides/400x240/1688741381729.jpg" alt="Deal image" height="240" width="400" loading="lazy"> </picture></div><div class="desc"><h4 class="desc_header">Things To Know</h4><p>&bull; Does Not Need A Satellite Dish<br /> &bull; Works With Any TV<br /> &bull; Ships With Latest Sky Remote<br />&bull; High Definition (HD) As Standard<br /> &bull; Requires 10Mbps Broadband<br />&bull; <a href="https://www.express.co.uk/li