port for HDR), it's remained largely unchanged since then.</p><p>This hugely-popular set-top box (seriously, there are <em>millions</em> of these plugged into TVs across the UK)&nbsp;still requires a satellite dish, which could be&nbsp;<em>perfect</em>&nbsp;if your home broadband speeds aren't quite speedy enough to stream&nbsp;<em>everything</em>&nbsp;to Sky Glass.</p><p>Sky recently increased the cost of Sky Q from &pound;28 to &pound;31 per month.</p><p>That's an additional &pound;54 over the course of a typical 18-month contract. Thankfully, there <em>is</em> still a way to save, thanks to&nbsp;<a data-link-tracking="InArticle|Link" href="https://www.awin1.com/awclick.php?gid=400877&amp;mid=11005&amp;awinaffid=213635&amp;linkid=3221548&amp;clickref=dxp" rel="nofollow" onclick="ExpressApp.GoogleAnalytics.TrackEvent('Affiliate NetworkEvent', 'AWIN')"><strong>our exclusive deal that drops the cost of Sky Q down to &pound;23 per month</strong></a> &ndash; making it comfortably the cheapest way to watch Sky TV.</p><p>While it might not be the latest kit from the Sky R&amp;D lab (you'll find yourself waiting for features that rolled out to Sky Glass and Sky Stream months earlier ...and that's if the features arrive at all), but Sky Q remains a solid set-top box. In fact, it earned a full&nbsp;<em>five stars</em>&nbsp;in our&nbsp;<a data-link-tracking="InArticle|Link" href="/sky-q-review" rel="tag"><strong>Sky Q review</strong></a>.&nbsp;</p></div><div class="buying-guide" id="buying-guide-11" data-id="11" data-single="1" data-name="Sky Q *UPDATED AUG 8, 23*"><div class="widget blurb"><div class="data"><h3 class="title">Sky Q</h3><h4 class="title">A Traditional Satellite Box, With Plenty Of Next-Generation Features</h4><div class="bg-stars" title="5 / 5"> <span class="star star-filled"></span> <span class="star star-filled"></span> <span class="star star-filled"></span> <span class="star star-filled"></span> <span class="star star-filled"></span></div><div class="colum