ITVX has been available on Sky Stream and Sky Glass since the streamer launched in late 2022.</p><p>However, these gadgets are both powered by Entertainment OS. In comparison, Sky Q relies on its own distinct operating system &ndash; even when this ageing hardware (Sky Q is the only set-top box in the Sky TV line-up that&nbsp;<em>still</em> requires a satellite dish and uses a physical hard-drive)&nbsp;<em>is</em>&nbsp;compatible with the same features as Glass and Stream, it takes some time for the same functionality to be developed and rolled-out to Sky Q viewers nationwide. Of course, not everything that's possible with the newer systems can be replicated on Sky Q, which is why you'll find some features missing compared to the latest set-top boxes.</p><p>The arrival of ITVX unlocks a&nbsp;<em>huge</em> amount of new content for Sky Q viewers. New boxsets created exclusively by ITV Studios for the streamer, like <em>A Spy Among Friends, Litvinenko</em>, and <em>Nolly</em>, as well as syndicated shows, such as&nbsp;<em>The Sex Lives Of College Girls</em>, have been inaccessible for Sky Q viewers until now. Given that ITV Hub was never available on Sky Q, some viewers will have&nbsp;<em>a lot</em> of catching up to do!</p></div><div class="text-description"><h2 id="Sky-Stream-and-Glass-TVs-get-huge-software-update-60557180" data-toc="0">Sky Stream and Glass TVs get huge software update</h2></div><div class="text-description"><p><strong>February 2, 2023</strong></p><p>Sky has started to roll out a mammoth software update to all Sky Stream and Sky Glass owners. Dubbed Entertainment OS 1.1, this update brings a number of hotly-anticipated features that Sky confirmed were in development in mid-2022.</p><p>Here's everything new included in Entertainment OS &ndash; the operating system that powers Stream and Glass. For those wondering, Sky Q is powered by an older version of Sky's custom-designed software and is updated on a different schedule. This ageing hardware &ndash; the only product still in the Sky TV lineup that requires a satellite dish &ndash; might not be able to handle all of the functionality listed below, we're still waiting on confirmation from Sky.</p><p><em>Personalised Playlists</em></p><blockquote><p>Playlists brings together everything you want to watch on Sky Stream or Sky Glass, including on-demand boxsets, recordings from live channels, shows from streamers like Netflix and Disney+, or Hollywood blockbusters. Until now, all household members would contribute to a single Playlist each time they pressed the '+' button on the remote.</p><p>With Entertainment OS 1.1, Sky Stream and Sky Glass owners can create up to five unique playlists &ndash; one for each member of your household, as well as a playlist for everyone to add things to enjoy together.</p><p>For families, it means you can keep all the episodes of <em>Paw Patrol</em>&nbsp;restricted to the kids&rsquo; lists, leaving yours free to fill with episodes of <em>The Last of Us</em>, <em>Gangs of London,</em> or <em>Below Deck</em> to watch when the children are asleep.</p></blockquote></div><div class="photo changeSpace"><p class="withoutCaption"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://cdn.images.express.co.uk/img/dynamic/59/940x/secondary/sky-entertainment-os-1-1-personalised-playlists-glass-stream-4550252.webp?r=1710321272104" media="screen"><img src="https://cdn.images.express.co.uk/img/dynamic/59/940x/secondary/sky-entertainment-os-1-1-personalised-playlists-glass-stream-4550252.jpg?r=1710321272104" alt="sky entertainment os 1.1 personalised playlists glass stream" title="sky entertainment os 1.1 personalised playlists glass stream" width="940" height="558" loading="lazy"></picture></p><span class="newsCaption">Sky Stream and Sky Glass owners can add shows to different Playlists for each household member <span class="caption">(Image: SKY)</span></span></div><div class="text-description"><p><em>New Voice Command</em></p><blockquote><p>Jumping back into what you want to watch has never been easier as Entertainment OS 1.1 adds the ability to use "Play" as a voice command. So, say &ldquo;Play&nbsp;<em>Love Island</em>&rdquo; to resume exactly where you left off in the South African villa or "Play&nbsp;<em>Top Gun: Maverick</em>" to launch the latest blockbuster adventure without navigating to a specific show page, your Playlist, or search results.</p><p>Until now, Sky Glass and Sky Stream owners had to search for a specific show, film, or sports fixture before they could select it using their voice.</p><p>As a reminder, Sky Glass supports hands-free voice commands so you won't even need to bother searching for a lost remote control to jump back into the latest episode of your new favourite binge-watch. If you watch using Sky Stream, you'll still be able to use the new "Play" voice control feature but you'll need to have your remote to hand and hold the microphone button.</p></blockquote><p><em>Spotlight On The Cast And Crew&nbsp;</em></p><blockquote><p>For the first time, Sky will highlight the cast and crew that worked on a particular TV show or film within its menu. If you want to see more from a particular actor, writer, or director, then simply click on thier headshot to see&nbsp;<em>everything</em> available to watch on Sky Glass or Sky Stream from that creator. This is similar to functoinality already available within Apple TV and Prime Video, but it's great to see it duplicated across the entire Sky TV catalogue.</p></blockquote><p><em>Bluetooth Boost</em></p><blockquote><p>For Sky Glass owners, Entertainment OS 1.1 bolsters Bluetooth connectivity so you can now listen via your Bluetooth headphones at the same time as Sky Glass&rsquo; speakers are playing. It means those who are heard of hearing can listen with their headphones, while watching with the rest of their household. This feature is not possible with Sky Stream, since that functionality is handled by your telly &ndash; not the box. You'll need to check with the manufacturer of your TV to see whether this is possible.</p></blockquote></div><div class="text-description"><h2 id="Amazon-Music-is-now-available-60557184" data-toc="0">Amazon Music is now available</h2></div><div class="text-description"><p><strong>January 25, 2023</strong></p><p>Amazon Music is now available as a standalone app on Sky Glass and Sky Stream. For those with a subscription to this Spotify rival, you'll be able to listen to millions of songs and albums via the Dolby Atmos soundbar built into Sky Glass (or whatever sound system you've got hooked-up to your Sky Stream box) for the first time.</p><p>Amazon Music offers thousands of hand-curated playlists as well as ad-free access to popular podcasts. To give it a go, simply say &ldquo;Hello Sky, open Amazon Music&rdquo; to your Sky Glass (if you have hands-free voice control enabled) or say &ldquo;Amazon Music&rdquo; into your voice remote on Glass or Stream to launch the app.</p><p>For a limited time, <a data-link-tracking="InArticle|Link" href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/music/unlimited?tag=dailexpr-21" rel="nofollow" onclick="ExpressApp.GoogleAnalytics.TrackEvent('Affiliate NetworkEvent', 'Amazon')"><strong>you can trial Amazon Music&nbsp;</strong></a><a data-link-tracking="InArticle|Link" href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/music/unlimited?tag=dailexpr-21" rel="nofollow" onclick="ExpressApp.GoogleAnalytics.TrackEvent('Affiliate NetworkEvent', 'Amazon')"><strong>for free</strong></a><a data-link-tracking="InArticle|Link" href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/music/unlimited?tag=dailexpr-21" rel="nofollow" onclick="ExpressApp.GoogleAnalytics.TrackEvent('Affiliate NetworkEvent', 'Amazon')"><strong> for one month</strong></a>.</p></div><div class="photo changeSpace"><p class="withoutCaption"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://cdn.images.express.co.uk/img/dynamic/59/940x/secondary/sky-glass-amazon-music-4550365.webp?r=1710321272203" media="screen"><img src="https://cdn.images.expre