currently available to new customers if you've been with the company for a while. And if you're out-of-contract, mentioning that you're thinking of leaving Sky TV could be a good way to unlock some new discounts... but you didn't hear that from us, <em>alright?</em></p></div><div class="text-description"><h2 id="Does-Sky-offer-Black-Friday-deals-60557206" data-toc="1">Does Sky offer Black Friday deals?</h2></div><div class="text-description"><p>Yes, Sky usually takes part in the annual Black Friday deals. These discounts are applied across a wide range of its products, including Sky Glass, Sky Stream, and fibre broadband packages. All of these Black Friday deals are available to&nbsp;<em>new</em> customers only. Existing customers who want to renegotiate their deal will need to call the Sky helpline on 03337590879.</p><p>That said, Black Friday doesn't&nbsp;<em>always</em> offer the lowest&nbsp;<em>ever</em> pricing on Sky Glass, Sky Stream, or Sky broadband. So don't wait for&nbsp;<em>months</em>&nbsp;until the latest Black Friday promotions come around as you might miss out on a much better deal available right now.</p></div><div class="text-description"><h2 id="How-Sky-TV-customers-can-cut-their-monthly-bills-60557208" data-toc="1">How Sky TV customers can cut their monthly bills</h2></div><div class="text-description"><p>When you sign-up for any of the deals currently on offer from Sky, there's a minimum term for the contract. Usually set at 18-months, this is the period in which you'll have to stick with the bundle that you added to your shopping basket on the day you signed-up.</p><p>However, as soon as that period is over, you'll be out-of-contract and able to renegotiate a new contract with Sky TV, continue paying each month without committing to a new minimum contract term (you'll usually find the monthly bills are quite a bit higher in this scenario), or leave Sky TV for another provider.</p><p>Under the current Ofcom rules, Sky <em>must</em>&nbsp;alert you when you're nearing the end of your current contract and have the above options open to you. It's at this stage in your contract when you'll be able to drop select channels or extras from your TV package &ndash; like Sky Cinema, for example &ndash; to lower your monthly bills. You might also be able to sign-up for a new deal (with another 18-month minimum contract term) to secure a discount or new extras for the same monthly cost.</p><p>If you're pretty set on leaving ...or at the very least, reducing the amount you pay each month, it's extremely likely that Sky will fight hard for your custom. Anecdotally, Sky customers regularly recount securing massive discounts and sweetheart deals when attempting to reduce the size of their telly package. After all, Sky will&nbsp;<em>really</em> want to keep existing customers like you ...it doesn't want to boost the subscriber count at rival Virgin Media. Of course, nothing is guaranteed.</p><p>Existing Sky TV customers can talk to a customer service representative by calling <strong>03337591018</strong>.</p><p>Worse case scenario, if you walk away from your Sky TV deal at the end of your current contract, wait a month or two, you'll be eligible to apply for the best Sky TV deals available to new customers all over again. And that is guaranteed to reduce the overall cost of your Sky TV package.</p></div><div class="photo changeSpace"><p class="withoutCaption"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://cdn.images.express.co.uk/img/dynamic/59/940x/secondary/best-sky-tv-deals-sky-q-with-remote-4062928.webp?r=1710321272496" media="screen"><img src="https://cdn.images.express.co.uk/img/dynamic/59/940x/secondary/best-sky-tv-deals-sky-q-with-remote-4062928.jpg?r=1710321272496" alt="best sky tv deals sky q with remote" title="best sky tv deals sky q with remote" width="839" height="558" loading="lazy"></picture></p><span class="newsCaption">Sky Q is the oldest set-top box in the lineup, but is the only one with a physical hard drive <span class="caption">(Image: SKY)</span></span></div><div class="text-description"><h2 id="Can-existing-Sky-TV-customers-get-the-same-deals-as-new-Sky-users-60557211" data-toc="1">Can existing Sky TV customers get the same deals as new Sky users?</h2></div><div class="text-description"><p>If you're already signed-up with Sky TV, you'll need to login to your account or ring the customer service helpline to discuss the deals available to you. Admittedly, there is a strong resemblance between the latest slew of existing customer deals and the new customer packages being advertised by Sky TV on its website. However, any free gifts used to tempt new customers are often dropped from the promotions available to existing Sky TV customers.</p><p>It's worth noting that existing Sky TV customers will save money on set-up fees, delivery, and won't need to wait for an engineer to get everything up-and-running (this only applies to Sky Q, with Sky Glass and Sky Stream easy enough that customers can set-up everything themselves to save time and money) since you're only haggling over price. That's one advantage that new Sky customers can't match.</p></div><div class="text-description"><h2 id="Can-you-watch-Sky-TV-for-free-60557213" data-toc="1">Can you watch Sky TV for free?</h2></div><div class="text-description"><p>Yes! For a limited time, <a data-link-tracking="InArticle|Link" href="https://www.awin1.com/cread.php?awinmid=11005&amp;awinaffid=213635&amp;campaign=&amp;clickref=Express---ExpressRated-&amp;clickref2=&amp;clickref3=&amp;clickref4=&amp;clickref5=&amp;clickref6=&amp;ued=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sky.com%2Fdeals%2Ftv&amp;pl=la" rel="nofollow" onclick="ExpressApp.GoogleAnalytics.TrackEvent('Affiliate NetworkEvent', 'AWIN')"><strong>Sky Stream is available&nbsp;</strong></a><a data-link-tracking="InArticle|Link" href="https://www.awin1.com/cread.php?awinmid=11005&amp;awinaffid=213635&amp;campaign=&amp;clickref=Express---ExpressRated-&amp;clickref2=&amp;clickref3=&amp;cl