he difference? Well, NOW is contract-free, so you won't need to worry about any minimum contract terms.</p><p>Instead, like Netflix and Disney+, you'll pay for access to the service each month via direct debit and can cancel and walk away&nbsp;<em>at any time.&nbsp;</em>Better yet, you can switch between the NOW Memberships available at any time. So, if you've finished bingeing a must-watch series and want to watch a few movies instead, you can switch from the Entertainment bundle to Sky Cinema for a month. Then, switch back whenever you want.</p></div><div class="photo changeSpace"><p class="withoutCaption"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://cdn.images.express.co.uk/img/dynamic/59/940x/secondary/best-sky-tv-deals-Sky-q-bundles-ultimate-tv-sky-q-lite-3958905.webp?r=1710321272569" media="screen"><img src="https://cdn.images.express.co.uk/img/dynamic/59/940x/secondary/best-sky-tv-deals-Sky-q-bundles-ultimate-tv-sky-q-lite-3958905.jpg?r=1710321272569" alt="best sky tv deals Sky q bundles ultimate tv sky q lite" title="best sky tv deals Sky q bundles ultimate tv sky q lite" width="833" height="558" loading="lazy"></picture></p><span class="newsCaption">The Sky Q set-top box is available in the Ultimate TV and Q Lite bundles <span class="caption">(Image: SKY)</span></span></div><div class="text-description"><p>NOW is the perfect solution for anyone who needs that extra flexibility. But if you're looking for the best way to watch all of the latest-and-greatest shows, movies and sports... you'd be better looking at Sky Q or Sky Glass. While the latter options support picture quality up to 4K Ultra HD, you'll need to pay extra to get 1080p HD from NOW. Not only that, you can't replicate features like Series Link, which automatically records new additions to a series whenever episodes air.</p><p>Voice controls are supported on both Sky Q, Sky Glass and NOW ...although only Glass supports hands-free commands. If you're watching NOW via an Apple TV or Fire TV, you'll have access to the same streaming services already available on Sky's own set-top boxes, including the likes of Netflix, Prime Video, Disney+, BBC iPlayer and more. However, unless you're subscribed to Sky Q or Sky Glass, you're not going to be able to bundle all of these subscriptions into a single monthly payment.</p></div><div class="text-description"><h2 id="Does-Sky-own-NOW-TV-60557220" data-toc="1">Does Sky own NOW TV?</h2></div><div class="text-description"><p>Sky Group - which owns most of Sky's product including Sky Glass, Sky TV and Sky Q - also own NOW TV. Despite being run by the same company, Sky tends to keep both products and brands away from each other - for reasons as we mentioned above.</p><p>Sky UK announced the launch of NOW TV in 2012 to take on the likes of Netflix by providing initally just films to an audience. However, NOW offers much more than it did way back in 2023 - offering sports, TV series and films like many other subscription services.</p><p>NOW allows people to buy "passes" to watch certain content like films, kids channels and more depending on what you want to indulge. NOW also allows you to stream on a number of different devices instead of being restricted to just a Sky box for example.</p><p>You can watch NOW on:</p><ul><li>Android devices and phones</li><li>iOS devices and phones</li><li>Xbox Series S and X&nbsp;</li><li>PS5</li><li>Apple TV</li><li>Chromecast</li><li>Samsung smart TVs</li><li>LG smart TVs</li></ul><p>NOW TV is a much more flexible way of watching TV which is why you'll struggle to find many Sky packages included with NOW TV.&nbsp;</p></div><div class="photo changeSpace"><p class="withoutCaption"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://cdn.images.express.co.uk/img/dynamic/59/940x/secondary/Best-Sky-Deals-New-Sky-Glass-Remote-3807267.webp?r=1710321272708" media="screen"><img src="https://cdn.images.express.co.uk/img/dynamic/59/940x/secondary/Best-Sky-Deals-New-Sky-Glass-Remote-3807267.jpg?r=1710321272708" alt="Best Sky Deals New Sky Glass Remote" title="Best Sky Deals New Sky Glass Remote" width="837" height="558" loading="lazy"></picture></p><span class="newsCaption">Voice commands let you quickly find the channel, show, director or actor you're hoping to watch next <span class="caption">(Image: SKY)</span></span></div><div class="text-description"><h2 id="Does-Sky-offer-discounts-for-pensioners-60557223" data-toc="1">Does Sky offer discounts for pensioners?</h2></div><div class="text-description"><p>Unfortunately, neither Sky TV nor its contract-free sister brand, NOW (formerly NOW TV), currently offers a special discount for&nbsp;pensioners. So, those hoping to secure a discount will be left disappointed. However, Sky offers a number of promotions throughout the year, so older viewers will likely be able to claim a discount in the sales, which will last the duration of the minimum term of their contract, which is usually 18-months or so.</p><p>But while there isn't a specific savings scheme for pensioners with Sky TV, the satellite telly firm does offer a number of extra provisions to help older customers. On <a data-link-tracking="InArticle|Link" href="https://www.awin1.com/cread.php?awinmid=11005&amp;awinaffid=213635&amp;clickref=Express---ExpressTech-&amp;ued=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sky.com%2Fhelp%2Farticles%2Fvulnerable-customers-guidelines" target="_blank" rel="nofollow" onclick="ExpressApp.GoogleAnalytics.TrackEvent('Affiliate NetworkEvent', 'AWIN')"><strong>a help page</strong></a>, Sky advises "We&rsquo;ve a range of support tools for customers who, for example, are elderly and need a little extra help, or who have particular accessibility needs (visual, hearing, cognitive or motor impairment)". It also has a dedicated page to support those who are struggling to pay their bills.&nbsp;</p><p>"Managing a budget can be hard at the best of times and, when circumstances change, paying bills on time might be difficult. If your payment&rsquo;s late, we&rsquo;ll send you reminders and give you another chance to pay us. We&rsquo;ll also add other safeguards to protect your interests. If a debt&rsquo;s left unpaid and is passed on to one of our debt collection agencies, they&rsquo;ll work with you to agree a fair and affordable repayment plan," it <strong><a data-link-tracking="InArticle|Link" href="https://www.awin1.com/cread.php?awinmid=11005&amp;awinaffid=213635&amp;clickref=Express---ExpressTech-&amp;ued=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sky.com%2Fhelp%2Farticles%2Fvulnerable-customers-guidelines" target="_blank" rel="nofollow" onclick="ExpressApp.GoogleAnalytics.TrackEvent('Affiliate NetworkEvent', 'AWIN')">advises</a></strong>. "Please let us know if you have trouble paying so we can help you. We understandably see our customers turning to family or friends to help them manage their affairs but, whether you&rsquo;re supporting someone else or need support yourself, it&rsquo;s best to act sooner rather than later."</p><p>"And if you&rsquo;re also struggling to pay other bills because, for example, your income&rsquo;s been lowered or you&rsquo;ve taken on some unexpected costs, it&rsquo;s always better to act as soon as you can to avoid falling further into debt. And whatever you need to do, we&rsquo;re here to help."</p></div><div class="text-description"><h2 id="Does-Sky-Stream-record-60557225" data-toc="1">Does Sky Stream record?</h2></div><div class="photo changeSpace"><p class="withoutCaption"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://cdn.images.express.co.uk/img/dynamic/59/940x/secondary/Does-Sky-Stream-record-5262879.webp?r=1710321272754" media="screen"><img src="https://cdn.images.express.co.uk/img/dynamic/59/940x/secondary/Does-Sky-Stream-record-5262879.jpg?r=1710321272754" alt="Does Sky Stream record?" title="Does Sky Stream record?" width="940" height="564" loading="lazy"></picture></p><span class="newsCaption">Does Sky Stream record? <span class="caption">(Image: THE MIRROR)</span></span></div><div class="text-description"><p>Sky Stream is Sky's newest invention which allows you to watch hundreds of Sky channels without needing to worry about wires or a satellite to plug in. <a data-link-tracking="InArticle|Link" rel="nofollow" href="https://www.awin1.com/cread.php?awinmid=11005&amp;awinaffid=213635&amp;campaign=&amp;clickref=---1532543-&amp;ued=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sky.com%2Fdeals%2Ffeatured&amp;platform=pl" onclick="ExpressApp.GoogleAnalytics.TrackEvent('Affiliate NetworkEvent', 'AWIN')"><strong>So it's no wonder that Sky Stream has become one of the more popular products</strong></a> to go for for UK households.</p><p>But one of the more popular things satellite box owners love to do is record their favourite shows so they don't miss any of their favourite series. So you might be wondering: does Sky Stream record?</p><p>Technically, the Sky Stream itself doesn't record shows like Sky Q does as there is nowhere to store the show and there's no harddrive to keep it on. But that doesn't matter because you can still stream most shows on demand through Sky and other apps.&nbsp;</p><p>Most devices and apps allow you to watch any previous show that was broadcast on the channel - for example the Channel 4 app will allow you to catch up on previous Taskmaster shows that you may have missed - and Sky Stream has this all built inside.&nbsp;</p></div><div class="text-description"><p><strong>READ NEXT<br></strong></p><ul><li><a data-link-tracking="InArticle|Link" href="/sky-glass-review" rel="tag"><strong>Sky Glass review</strong></a></li><li><a data-link-tracking="InArticle|Link" href="/sky-q-review" rel="tag"><strong><strong>Sky Q review</strong></strong></a></li><li><a data-link-tracking="InArticle|Link" href="/sky-stream-review" rel="tag"><strong><strong>Sky Stream review</strong></strong></a></li><li><a data-link-tracking="InArticle|Link" href="/life-style/science-technology/1548139/best-vpn" rel="tag"><strong>Best VPN</strong></a></li></ul></div></div></div> </article><div class="article-elements"><div class="clearfix related_entities tags-element"> <a href="/latest/sky" class="related_entity" data-link-tracking="EndArticle|Tag|Sky" onclick="ExpressApp.GoogleAnalytics.TrackEvent('Article Entities', '/latest/sky')">Sky</a> <a href="/latest/sky-broadband" class="related_entity" data-link-tracking="EndArticle|Tag|Sky Broadband" onclick="ExpressApp.GoogleAnalytics.TrackEvent('Article Entities', '/latest/sky-broadband')">Sky Broadband</a></div> <footer class="mainFooter cf" id="mainFooter"> </footer></div></div> <script src="https://cdn.images.express.co.uk/js/dist/compare-prices20240429.min.js" defer></script> <script src="https://cdn.images.express.co.uk/js/dist/affiliate-widgets20240429.min.js" defer></script> </div><div class="mainFooter clearfix size"> <aside><div class="search-form"><p class="header">SEARCH</p><div class="clearfix"><form action="/search" method="post"> <label> <input type="search" placeholder="Search..." class="with-shadow" name="query" id="search_query_footer"> </label> <button type="submit" class="with-shadow" name="submit" aria-label="Search"><var></var></button></form></div></div><div class="social-media-buttons"><p class="header">CONNECT WITH US</p><ul class="clearfix"><li> <a href="https://www.facebook.com/DailyExpress" rel="external" class="social-icons facebook" >Find us on Facebook</a></li><li> <a href="https://twitter.com/daily_express" rel="external" class="social-icons twitter">Follow us on Twitter</a></li><li> <a href="https://www.instagram.com/dailyexpress" rel="external" class="social-icons instagram">Follow us on Instagram</a></li><li> <a href="https://story.snapchat.com/p/8d40c61d-5ce5-4aa1-ae7f-5dc02d1e86a2/2619291367686145" rel="external" class="social-icons snapchat">Follow us on Snapchat</a></li><li> <a href="https://www.youtube.com/user/theexpressonline" rel="external" class="social-icons youtube">Check our YouTube channel</a></li><li> <a href="/feeds" class="social-icons rss">Subscribe to our rss f